You can't tell from the title of this movie, but this is part of the Emmanuelle Through Time series of Cinemax After Dark features.  This particular feature was never shown on Cinemax (probably because of the songs and rather unconvincing lip-synching - not your typical Skinemax fare) but make no mistake, it's the same cast and cheesy special effects.  DailyGrindhouse.com has a great interview with Director Rolfe Kanefsky that gives you all the background you could want on this DVD and the entire Emmanuelle Through Time series of seven features.  In the interview, Kanefsky explains that since producer Alain Siritzky's death in 2014, his estate being settled has delayed any release of the hundreds of films that Siritzky was involved with.  Kanefsky does not however, explain how this movie got released.

I'm guessing the Adventures Into The Woods title is a play on the 2014 Meryl Streep/Johnny Depp adaptation of the Sondheim fairy tale musical Into The Woods.

Anyway, this movie itself hearkens back to Charles Band's Cinderella or Bill Osco's Alice In Wonderland in that it has a dozen clever, peppy, filthy songs to go along with lots of naked flesh and characters and stories from your childhood.  It's all great fun and the cast looks like they were having a blast with the costumes and dance numbers.

Here's to hoping that somehow, all of the Emmanuelle Through Time features get released on DVD eventually.  That would be an instant purchase for me for sure.
